age?topicID=204.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showMessage?topicID=199.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=95%><tr><td bgcolor=#464646><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#213d87 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#213d87 class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uceldor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celdor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ultrafx.com/note.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1182<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/17/01 4:18:15 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.austin.rr.com/mav1973/aegishjalmr.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: reply to thread</span><hr size=1> People keep saying they don't want to go for whatever reason. What these people need to realize is, NOW IS THE TIME TO MAKE YOUR REASONS HEARD. But once the gverment decides a course of action that the majority of our nation agrees on and if that action requires a draft (something I doubt due to the massive reserves and volunteers we would have), then you shut up about your personal opinion and you go to serve your country. <br>
<br>
If you don't, then you are not American. You can say what you will about personal freedom of decision, but when your country calls you go. Even if you disagree. Otherwise you can run and basically abandon your country and people. But don't complain 20 years from now when those people still consider you a coward and the country you abandoned does not want you back. You make your decision freely, but don't think you can run and then show back up a few years after the war and its 'game on, lets continue as if nothing ever happened'. <br>
<br>
Main point reiterated: Express your discontent now and be heard, but if once we have our course of action then follow it. If you don't, you are a Traitor by our law and deserve treatment in accordance with your crime. And if you don't think that running from a draft makes you a traitor, I suggest you contact a lawyer and verify.<br>
<br>
ps. you could still serve the 5 years for refusing to take up arms and remain an american. I find it sad that anyone would consider giving up their citizenship instead. Read 'Man Without a Country' sometime. <p><small><br><br><br>Ægishjalm eg ber milli bruna mjer.<b> - Icelandic Chant</b></small></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utriff.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Triff</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.maclem.com/images/triff/triffdot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 321<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/17/01 5:14:18 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.maclem.com/images/triff/trifflogo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Okay</span><hr size=1> This'll probably be my last post on this, although I'll likely watch this post. If you find it too long to actually read, that's fine, but don't respond to it then.<br>
<br>
Let me start by defining the terms I'm arguing about, since a lot of you are misunderstanding what I'm getting at, and I figure I haven't made myself clear enough yet. I am not arguing about whether or not America should do anything about what happened (although incidentally, I think America certainly should). I'm not trying to argue whether or not this should bring about a war. I never said it is wrong to fight for what you value, when it becomes necessary.<br>
<br>
This entire thing, for me, is a protest to a government that wants to force people to fight for them—the draft—and about the root of that, which is basically altruism. Altruism is the belief that selflessness is a virtue; that men should serve one another. All references to unquestioning obedience (&quot;duty&quot;) owed to others is a form of altruism. I disagree with every premise of that. I stand by the fact that when one man eats, it is only he that is nourished, and no one else, no matter how much he eats. Humans are not a collective whole. We are individuals, no matter how much anyone tries to change this.<br>
<br>
There are people whose aim is to make themselves happy. They do this because it is painfully obvious that making oneself happy is pleasurable.<br>
<br>
There are people who enjoy helping others. They do it for the knowledge and feeling of making someone happy. This amounts to doing it to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> make themselves happy</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Let me say that if I was to have someone beside me in a war, I'd sure as hell prefer the man who has the self-respect to think and live for himself (and to protect with a passion all things that influence this) over a man who doesn't think that he is worth enough to fight for (which is indeed the definition of &quot;selfless&quot;), and that the final arbiter of everything is what the majority thinks.<br>
<br>
When people speak of serving the majority, or society, or the public, or the whole, or the collective, or whatever name they wish to give it, do you ever stop to think of the exact meaning of those terms? When someone speaks to someone else of it, they refer to that all-important majority that is defined as being made up of &quot;everyone—except you.&quot; Follow that logic. What that basically leads to is the conclusion that nobody has self-worth. If you are not worth anything, then what could be good in my helping you? What could be good about a majority made up of people who are worthless?<br>
<br>
I don't follow that line of &quot;thought.&quot; I understand that all groups of people are groups of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> individuals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. I hold that the only worth that can be derived from someone is by his will to live for himself.<br>
<br>
Then there are people that will say I should love and care for everyone equally. This is horribly wrong. Anyone who loves everyone equally has no values. What it amounts to is someone saying that the greatest man is equal to the most worthless beggar.<br>
<br>
I'm not going into some debate about whether I am objectively more important than anyone else—that has no place in this specific argument. What I am saying is that I am important to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> myself</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Think of this in broader terms than you have been. That I am important to myself does not mean I have no regard for others; it simply means I am not willing to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> sacrifice</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> myself for others.<br>
<br>
When I say &quot;sacrifice,&quot; I mean it as taking a loss. I do not think of it as a sacrifice to work hard in order to earn one's keep, as I've heard it being referred to. To paraphrase Ayn Rand, it isn't a sacrifice to do without certain luxuries in order to feed your baby, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> if</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> you care more about sustaining and nourishing your baby than you do for having said luxuries. It <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> is</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a sacrifice, though, to let your baby die in order to feed the neighbor's baby instead, if you personally cared more for your baby than for your neighbor's.<br>
<br>
Do you see more clearly what I am getting at? So long as you are comprehending what it is I am arguing, I really don't care if you disagree with me. What this means is that you have no grounds to call me a coward. The term that most of you will be looking for (if you haven't found it already) is &quot;selfish,&quot; although I take pride in the title while you will mean to condemn me with it. With that said, let me get to responding to all these posts...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Muzaak:<br>
I only hope you learn something about loyalty before it is too late for you. We all someday face our enemies and they never are our own.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->My very being is the antithesis of &quot;loyalty.&quot; I have no respect for someone's ability to obey, as it takes no thought or conviction to do so (fast proof: a dog can do it). And who is to say that we never face our own enemies? Why would anyone face anything else? If someone comes and tries to harass my girlfriend, he becomes <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> my</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> enemy as well as hers, because I value her. So when I go to main this person who is harassing her, I do it out of self-interest. It is not selfless.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Kytherion:<br>
And yet you will seek to derive the benefit. The luxuries you've enjoyed, the freedom you've had, the society from which you have received protection all of your life...and you'll flee when your turn comes. You might tell yourself that you've earned these things through working hard and paying taxes, as if punching a time clock or getting a college degree is difficult.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Let me say again that those people didn't give me freedom. They fought those who were trying to take freedom away. Depending on each individual that was there, they may or may not have been specifically aiming to keep everyone in the future safe as well. But it wasn't a contract that was offered to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> me</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to sign. I owe them nothing, and what I choose to do in their memory is up to me alone.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Lanarie:<br>
Do you think America would be the same place if it would have sat by and coward in the corner during the two world wars while Europe was decimated? Should we have just ignored the attack on Pearl Harbor?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Did I ever say people should have sat back? The people who signed up for the military went and fought. I respect that. But they made their choice and I made mine.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Caoilfhionn:<br>
Something tells me you'd have been sitting there with your head between your knees trying not to puke. It's just a feeling I get.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Come back when you learn to speak in thoughts, and not feelings. I can't even ask why you think that, because you made it apparent you won't be giving any logical reasons.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Caoilfhionn:<br>
I suppose you would have stood on the street pondering how important this was to your day to day life, and whether or not this act justified your moving to a fellow humans assistance. I suppose you'll come back at me and tell me that it was their job. Well, I can tell you I've seen numerous reports of every day citizens, not rescue workers, going above and beyond, instead of hiding in their closets, as you'd have us believe is the right thing to do.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Um...no. I'm well aware that a lot of people love to help others. I never said there's anything wrong with it; I respect them for doing what they decided they wanted to do. What's wrong is when you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> expect</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> everyone to have a love of helping others.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Caoilfhionn:<br>
Tell me. When does this become your fight? When it's your sister? When the building your mother works in crumbles to the ground? When the house next door to you is bombed? God forbid, when you yourself are attacked? Based on your principles, I should get some damn popcorn and watch your house burn to the ground, solely on the basis that, hey, I don't know you, you don't affect me, and why should I stick my neck over the line for you?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->It becomes my fight when there is an apparent threat to me and all I care about. If you live next door to me some day, and terrorists come and burn my house down, and you sit out on your porch and watch without doing a thing, I won't harbor any anger for you. I don't think that you or anyone else are required to serve my interests over your own. If your personal interest includes saving those around you, go ahead. You'll make those people happy. But don't yell at me if I have no desire to make everyone I meet happy, and refuse to sacrifice myself for others' happiness.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Poppen Steelfist:<br>
Now let me look at your and Triff's response...and I'm gonna sum it up for brevity.<br>
<br>
&quot;Whew! Wasn't me thank God! ..What!? we gonna fight to defend ourselves!?..OH SHIT I'm Outta here!&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I made no mention of fighting to defend myself. This is all about being drafted. Do at least you understand that rebelling against a draft is a form of fighting to defend myself and my freedom?<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Poppen Steelfist:<br>
Man I'm sorry but both you and Triff are very very chickenshit. Americans die and now that our country has a need for its fighting force you tell us that you would rather run away than do your duty? And IT IS YOUR DUTY! Both you and Triff must understand you don't live here for free. None of us do. If the country needs you..and calls you..you fucking go. Simple..clear cut..case closed. Why don't you and Triff tell the 5000+ plus innocents who died Tuesday that you don't care to fight for their memory? Why don't you visit a school and tell the young school children you don't have the testicular fortitude to be men and defend them.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Case closed? Aren't you going to at least tell me <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> why</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I owe my life to the government? Sorry, but I don't consider someone else's &quot;need&quot; as a claim upon anyone's work or time. And I see your comments at the end as an attempt to guilt me. I bet you're not counting on me to say that I could tell both those who died and those school children that I am not willing to fight for the memory of those who died, nor to protect them, if I have no personal interest in them. My interest is in fighting for myself if it comes to that.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Poppen Steelfist:<br>
When you guys grow up a bit you will understand. I have a three year old son. He's the love of my life, all I really have basically. I could never look him in the eyes and say &quot;I'm not enough of a man to defend you son&quot;. You apparently don't have anyone that you are willing to die for do you Triff and Glade? If that's the case I'm sorry you both live such isolationist lives. When your own children, parents, loved ones, and threatened..you will act..you have to if you are human. I consider all American people to be my brothers and sisters. Black, White, Islamic, Jewish. I will not stand before them and tell them that I wish to live and enjoy the fruits of this country but I am too scared for my own life to fight for what we believe in. This type of post frankly sickens me guys..please rethink where you stand and lose your selfishness..if you die in war so be it..if I die in war so be it..at least I know my son can grow to manhood safely becuase I had the balls to defend my country.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I will fight to protect what I care about. That's not the problem. What I am saying is that that I care about my personal interests far more than I do about all the others. You are apparently making no distinction between your son and everyone else in the country. I'm not afraid to fight for my ideals, but I'm not willing to be forced to fight for anyone else.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Kytherion:<br>
So which is it, Gladetree? I mean, is this a post-teenage angsty civil liberties issue, or are you just unable to see eye to eye with the Pres on this little debate?<br>
<br>
Shit, why didn't you say so? We'll make sure the Supreme Allied Commander consults with you before he does anything! We wouldn't want to deploy forces without your fine strategic insight. Make sure you leave us your new number in Canada.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->So what you're saying is that the American thing to do is obey, obey, obey and don't question? Is that your idea of a hero?<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Did the Americans curl up into a ball and whine like spoiled children when presented with the daunting task of taking on the Nazi's or Imperial Japan? Or how about our Revolutinary forefathers taking on the British Empire?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->So far I haven't seen anyone at all say they should've.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Lanarie:<br>
No one said things will be easy. And I'm not just talking about things from a military standpoint, but also from a socio-political one. Yes, I'm afraid you may have to give up the SUV if the gas prices get too high, or if gas reserves are required for the war effort. Or, you will have to learn to have patience and realize the world doesn't revolve around &quot;You&quot;<br>
<br>
Too many people have had things so easy in their lives that they expect everything to be handed to them on a silver platter. I sound like a friggen old-timer, but you know what, this is the absolute truth.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I'm not asking people to give things to me. What I am doing is refusing to fight for anyone except myself.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Lanarie:<br>
Its time to grow up folks, and realize that nothing great is accomplished without hard work or sacrifice. Its shame that too many are too self-centered to realize this.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->See what I said about sacrifice. Hard work is put forth to achieve goals. Sacrifices are put forth to destroy individuals. There's a difference, and I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> am</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> working hard, myself.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Bordon:<br>
America gave you the right to live here freely. HOWEVER, if your country calls upon you to defend it's borders, then damnit you better answer the call. Don't expect others to carry your load.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->America didn't give me my rights. Every reasoning being is born with them, and a man's rights should never be taken away from him unless he violates the rights of someone else. What the American military did was defend its citizens' rights from being revoked by others. And I'm not asking anyone else to go fight for me. It's their own decision to fight.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Bordon:<br>
I will not tolerate &quot;non-team&quot; players.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Contextual translation: &quot;I will not tolerate anyone who doesn't do what the government tells him to do.&quot;<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Lukaria Trueheart:<br>
Triff, in the end, what you have been saying is that your life is more important than anyone else's.<br>
<br>
You would let my son die before you lifted a hand to help because you don't know him.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I never said my life is more important than anyone else's. I said <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> I</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> value my life and my interests above everyone else's. And in all actuality, if I, personally, saw your son coming to some peril, and helping him wasn't obvious suicide, I'd probably help him because it would make me happy to do so. But thank you for understanding that I should not required to help you or him if I don't want to.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Lanarie:<br>
My whole point is not drum up support for all out war, just to inform people that it is their DUTY to their country as citizens to serve if they are called upon.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->And my whole point is to tell you that I owe you nothing.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Muzaak:<br>
I can't expect all US citizens to feel the same horror I felt when I heard news that the WTC was gone with all the people in it, but I can certainly expect every US citizen to stand behind the troops that eventually go to war to protect this country.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I will stand behind those troops if their target is chosen logically. I won't stand behind the government's decision if Bush sends them somewhere stupid. I think for myself.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Lanarie:<br>
