It takes courage to accept that before you harm another human being, you would let them kill you.  It takes even more courage to accept that this may mean the death of your loved ones.  This is why the USA offers the status of Consciencious Objector.  Some people know themselves well enough to know that they simply could not bring themselves to harm another human.  These people do not belong in the armed forces, but that does not make them cowards.<br>
