-- Sister Zariel <p><center><img src="http://www.fluidshockwave.homestead.com/files/zarrysig.jpg"> <BR> <BR> <a href="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg/sanhedrin">Sanhedrin</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uogmuk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ogmuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 483<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/17/01 8:41:19 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /bow</span><hr size=1> *deleted posts on request from author* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/umirrielle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mirrielle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/17/01 8:48:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My two coppers</span><hr size=1> /blink<br>
<br>
wow.<br>
<br>
I've read this thread through with some interest and I'm not in the habit of contributing to rants.  But I'm going to this time.<br>
<br>
This is obviously a highly charged topic.  One that is difficult to argue no matter which side of the issues you are on.  Here are my thoughts <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Draft Dodgers:  People refuse to fight when their country declares war for a variety of reasons including religious conviction, philosophical differences, self interest ... the two themes that I've seen mentioned here appear to point to the latter examples.  And the reality is, there is nothing to be said to them that will change their minds.  Personal attacks serve only to make them dig in their heels and defend their choice more adamantly.  <br>
<br>
The truth is either you see this as an attack on Americans and take it personally as an American.  Or you see it as an attack on the freedoms for which America stands and there fore on yours or your communities freedoms.  Or you see it as an attack on the United States as a disembodied symbol and establishment to which you have little or no connection regardless of your residence.<br>
<br>
How will you as an individual know there is enough proof to 'go after' the individuals or organizations responsible?  I don't think you can.  Among other things, you aren't willing or capable of collecting the evidence, compiling it, and drawing conclusions.  That is part of what we expect our government and its resources to do for us.  We elect representatives and a president and ask them to review the information placed before them and to take appropriate actions.  Part of being a citizen of a democratic rebublic is trusting those who we have put in power to do the right thing, at the right time.  Does this mean we should blindly follow or grant them carte blanche?  No.  Does this abrogate our responsibility to pay attention and be as informed as possible about what is happening in the world?  Of course not.  But we also should avoid jumping to conclusions about what should and should not be done and how we will or will not support it.  The point can be argued ad nauseum during this period of fear and anger, but its all wind in the dark until all the evidence is in and a decision has been made.  I doubt The United States will do anything dramatic without the support not only of her own citizens but the international community.<br>
<br>
What IS the correct action to take?  Well, actually this is an unecessary question.  We want Justice.  We want the individuals and organizations responsible to be punished.  We want those who supported and harbor the guilty to also suffer for protecting those who have murdered innocents.<br>
<br>
The issue really turns on the question of collateral damage.  How much are we willing to accept?<br>
<br>
Do you really believe that our government or the people who support it want to murder innocents in order to bring the guilty to justice?   I don't.  But I am aware that minimizing the possiblility of causing the death of those who are themselves victims of terrorists or innocent bystanders means that justice will not be a swift as my anger would like it to be.  My thirst for vengence is dissatisfied by the possiblility that some of the perpetrators of this atrocity might get to live a long while, and that some, as sick as it makes me feel, some might even get away with it, and pass their social illness on to others.  However I have to believe that the majority will be punished.<br>
<br>
Another reality is that the world is not a perfect place and never has been.  As great as the United States is, as many friends as we have in the International community, we cannot deny the fact that there are also those who hate us with a fervor that burns like the fires of Hell.   And this past week - we were shaken from our complacency and forced to recognize this to be true.  What we cannot and must not allow these terrorists to do is to fracture our unity or break our resolve to persevere and prosper. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukytherion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kytherion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 246<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/17/01 9:02:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well...</span><hr size=1> &quot;Not everyone who chooses not to fight is a coward. Some people are forbidden by their religion to go to war -- for example, the Quakers.&quot;<br>
<br>
Indeed. There are many positions in the armed forces which do not place the soldier in the position of having to kill anyone.<br>
<br>
I think I recall a certain field medic who served in the Pacific during WW2. A 7th Day Adventist I believe...I'm pretty sure he was awarded the Medal of Honor. Kept charging into enemy fire to pull out the wounded.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, I'm personally acquainted with a Jehovah's Witness. According to him, they aren't allowed to be involved at all. I admit I'm not all that keen on going off to fight while he wanders around knocking on people's doors to distribute religious pamphlets.<br>
<br>
It's a fine line, I think. Serving your country doesn't necessarily mean inflicting violence on others, but it does mean service.<br>
<br>
If it were up to me, I'd say that Adventist can stitch me up anytime, and that Jehovah's Witness can distribute copies of The Watchtower while he's in prison and/or France. But that may be a bit hard line. =)<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uxenedrae01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xenedrae01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/17/01 9:02:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A is A</span><hr size=1> Among all the posts I have read here, there are but a scarce few of you that I would want defending My freedom.  ..the true conflict here is not Whether to fight for freedom or not, but Why (and therefore, When) one fights for freedom.<br>
<br>
For you people that 'think' that this great country was founded based on 'selfless service and sacrifice for the sake of others:'<br>
<br>
I suggest you Think again.  They fought for themselves...and the freedom of the rest was a concern, but NOT the prime justification.  These men committed treason.  It was not to be taken lightly.  They knew it and did it anyway, because they, themselves, were not willing to sacrifice their <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> own</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> lives as a means to the ends of others. ...and I for one am glad, grateful and solemnly proud of their choice of battles.  But it only means something to me because they didn't have to do it, they chose to.  They did not do it for me and I don't delude myself into pretending they did--nor would I want them to!!!!  Patrick Henry did <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> say &quot;Give them liberty or give me death&quot;  ... he said &quot;...I know not what course others may take; but as for me, give me liberty or give me death!&quot;<br>
<br>
They also used the best technology available to them at the time.  <br>
<br>
Glade, we <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> do</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> know where the terrorists are; we've known for a long time which countries make a practice of harboring terrorists and condoning terrorism against freedom.  'We have the technology' -let us now use it.  We should bomb every man, woman, child and animal in those countries.  I don't know about the rest of you, but that woman (on the west bank celebrations) on TV saying how she wished all of her children would grow up to be that brave told me exactly how deep their hatred of us (representatives of freedom) runs and how well we need to exterminate them, their families, their children and those that hide and or protect them ...even those who don't openly agree with them yet actively hide them.  But a 'prolonged military campaign' is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the answer.  ..it smells strongly of propaganda, and yes it will cost many unnecessary American (and potentially ally) causualties of war.  4,700+ is more than enough Americans dead already. This BS can be taken care of once and for all.  'We have the technology'<br>
<br>
Triff's post advocates nothing more (and nothing less!!) than rational self-interest, as our founding fathers also advocated.  Their commitment was to the principle of <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> individual</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> rights, and of fighting off the yoke of tyrants.  Triff hasn't said he wouldn't fight; he's said he doesn't recognize your (or anyone's) 'right' to sacrifice him for their (your or your child's) sake.  The winning team will be made of such people, a team of individuals; each fighting for his own rights, freedom and life.  Americans.<br>
<br>
Here's an Ayn Rand quote for ya:<br>
&quot;What most people are evading today is the realization that under the lip service they are paying to an anti-totalitarian crusade, they have accepted all the basic premises of a totalitarian philosophy.&quot;<br>
<br>
How ironic that those throwing the word 'coward' around so much are themselves the moral cowards.<br>
<br>
For any of you who might be interested in authors that hold/held beliefs supporting <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> individual</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> rights, I'd suggest reading articles/books/etc. by Aristotle, Ethan Allen, Patrick Henry, John Locke, Thomas Jefferson, Thomas Paine, Elihu Palmer, Ayn Rand, Ludwig von Mises, George Washington.  (you opposers -to subservience of the individual to the collective- may wish to read up on Your philosophical forefathers: Hitler, Kant, Lenin, Marx just to name a few) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uaphroditex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aphroditex</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#E9D756>(9/17/01 9:08:45 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://mayuan.ntsj.com/gohanssj2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well...</span><hr size=1> Don't get me wrong, I personally could never bring myself to actually kill someone, but it will not preclude me being there when my country calls me to defend the freedom that has been handed to me.  Whatever way I can serve that does not conflict with my beliefs is what I will do, whether it be design (I'm currently studying aerospace engineering and space science), or simple data correlation for intellegence purposes, I will help in whatever way possible. <p><a href=http://afflictionguild.com/scripts/member.x?username=Aphroditex&charactername=Aphroditex>Aphroditex Bubblefists</a></b>;  Serenity Z'Chaotic; Pickett Pocketts<BR>
